<br>
The &quot;unfair&quot; advantage comes from being able to use resources on your computer that other players would not normally have access to.  What someone does with those resources is not what is important.  The fact that you have them in the first place is what gives you the &quot;unfair&quot; advantage.<br>
<br>
Someone could also say the same thing about using two computers on the same network sharing the same bandwidth.  The difference here though is that VI can not monitor nor can they prohibit the use of a second computer using seperate resources while their software is not running on one machine completely free of all 3rd party software.<br>
<br>
What VI can do is prohibit the modification of any information packet sent across your network to and from the VI network.  What VI does with this regulation is prohibit the use of third party software used to modify the information sent to and from the VI network.  What they can't do is prohibit you from reading the information they send and recieve.  Why?  Because that is exactly what their software was desingned to do.<br>
<br>
Now using programs such as showeq is not addressed in the Everquest EULA.  However... should a pagen choose to curse and shun god they usually get struck with lightning.  Hence VI is the overall end all solution to all of their problems.<br>
<br>
The EULA is the equivilant of a sign in a store that says the following...<br>
<br>
&quot;We reserve the right to refuse business to anyone.&quot;<br>
<br>
and they have that right. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=193604">My Stuff</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E7D7B5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/ualthalustherogue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Althalus The Rogue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star_white.gif>MMDN CSC Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 188<br> <font color=#330000>(5/23/02 7:25:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm41.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=810.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Yes this program works and yes you can run 2 copies of EQ on the same PC in separate windows.<br>
